				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: L Abilities: 2 Questions <a name="29364"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 22 04 12:05 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm afraid I can't answer your questions but.... I would suggest, if you've not seen it in action, you reconsider on the Designate MA ability. Its only 4 points so its pretty easy to get and its really helped me a lot.
<br />

<br />
1) You know exactly when the MA (normally the MT too) has targeted the mob. I find this useful in pickup groups especially
<br />

<br />
2) When you pull adds (which I do a fair bit on normal LDoNs) you know which mob the MA is going for right away. It is extremely clear and obvious to everybody in the group. I find this a great aid when mezzing, also find it somewhat useful as a shaman so I can malos the mob being mezzed.
<br />

<br />
Lots of people say &quot;pah, I just use /assist&quot;. Well, that's great if you WANT to assist on the MA's mob. The delegate MA skill though, is really useful for people who want to target the other mobs - to debuff, mezz, root or whatever. That to me is where its real strength lies.
<br />

<br />
On the regen question - I would check if this counts towards capped regen (and similarly for FT) before spending points on it. I have a feeling it might do.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
