				<td colspan="2"><span>&quot;1. Health of Target's Target - Can anyone give a detailed comment about what they actually see when they use this, and why they would even use it. 
<br />

<br />
2. Health Regeneration - Is it 1 point per ability level or more ? 
<br />

<br />
I do nothing except LDoN and I am almost always the group leader so the leadership points fall like rain, in normal adventure, I'm the puller, slower, mezer,and haster so designateing an MA isn't a huge deal for me. It would be cool if the hp regen is more than 1 hps to break 30 hps standing regen out of sheer boredom&quot;
<br />

<br />
1.  I have this.  Everyone likes it.  It takes some getting used to useing it though.
<br />

<br />
2.  Its one point per level.  Which is nice if you have NH3 Innate Regen 3 and items and augs with regen.
<br />

<br />
DMA is very good and gives me a bigger picture of whats going on.  It also doesn't cost very much and I am always leader.  Getting points is easy and I lost count of how many I have.  Spell Awareness is also very nice.  That gives you an idea of what mobs and people in your group are casting.  When noob ranger forgets to snare, you can throw in a snare before mob runs away.  Also you will know when a mob is trying to heal.  There are some useless leader points, but I'm sure I'll end up getting them all.
<br />

<br />
Conaden Darksong, 65 Human Maestro
