				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: L Abilities: 2 Questions <a name="31397"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 29 04 1:25 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have a normal weekend xp group, and we have the cleric bot set up as the leader always. I don't personally have any leadership abilities, but we all chose which to get and got the following in this order: 
<br />

<br />
1) Designate MA. Love it. Two ways to see who the MA has targetted (npc name has &gt;&gt; Mean Mob &lt;&lt; around it) and the ring which is different from the targetting ring. It's obvious which to mezz, which can be really helpful when you have a clump of the exact same mobs... hit assist, get it, they all shift just a bit as you're targetting the add, they're all taking damage on DS... hit assist to make sure that IS the add, target it again.. bleh. Now you can see right away which is the add, and it's clear as day even in clumps!
<br />

<br />
2) Health of Target's Target. Also love it. You have to open the window each time, and it doesn't seem to remember where I stick it on my screen so have to move it each time, but maybe they'll fix that. Can see immediately if the mob changes from the MT to a caster, and let loose a bellow to stun it. And the MT can see right away they lost aggro and get it back fast. The bar does not update until the mob has a chance to attack however. As in, a mezzed mob will always report the person they had targetted when they got mezzed. As soon as mez is broken, it updates. 
<br />

<br />
3) Spell Awareness (is that what it's called again?). This was more for fun. I like seeing what spells are being cast, and is useful to know when a stun would be very important. And how long you have to interrupt (complete heal, well, we can let it cast for 6 seconds or so to reduce damage it does before interrupting). 
<br />

<br />
Those are the three clericbot has now. She's the one we designate as Raid Leader on raids, and she'll get Designate MA then. Since we're not a raiding guild, but a casual guild that raids, it's a slow road for those! </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
